{
  "name": "RPlog_Back_from_Prison",
  "title": "Back from Prison",
  "summary": "Aboard the sanctuary ship Refrain of Anshalar, the Jedi Aurejin returns from a long, harrowing absence to reunite with his pregnant wife Jessalyn Valios in their garden quarters. Over carefully brewed ginger tea, the two share their worries about the mysterious Domani, the absence of word from Leia, and the troubled Mailyn Raines, who clings to the Selas Simon's dark view of the Jedi. Aurejin delights in sensing his unborn son and vows to stop blaming himself for Mailyn's hatred. Their apprentice Kyyel joins them, reporting that he intends to help Han search for clues and reflecting honestly on his diminished but lingering anger toward Mailyn, satisfying Aurejin that he is 'staying within the square.' Jessalyn reveals her own plan to accompany the search and infiltrate Domani by posing as a Jedi seeking to learn, before Aurejin retires to finally shed his beard and prison clothes and the three settle in to share a meal.",
